\par\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\ltrch\loch \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93In order to use the identify skill, you must first focus your attention on the thing you want to identify. You must be able to see it with your perception skill as well as your mana sense,\u8221\'94 the Guide began explaining. \u8220\'93Think of it as seeing all of the thing in question, both its physical and metaphysical existence. Once you can get a glimpse of that gestalt, the System will step in provide you additional information, unlocking the beginner level of the identify skill.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The Guide waved a hand and the staff Marcus had used earlier appeared on the ground in front of him. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Use this to work on the technique, it\u8217\'92s not as easy as it sounds.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Marcus did as instructed, focusing his full attention on the staff without touching it. This skill was focused on seeing, not on tactile contact after all. He spent several minutes staring intently at the object, seeing the mana construct inside it as if it were overlaid on it. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You\u8217\'92re trying too hard,\u8221\'94 the Guide chided gently. \u8220\'93Relax your focus. Think of this as more of taking a quick snapshot of the object than trying to paint a portrait of it in your head.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 He forced himself to relax and close his eyes for a few moments. Then he tried again, focusing both his eyes and mana senses simultaneously this time. This time, instead of seeing one aspect of it overlaid with the other, he saw it as one complete object. There was more to its mana than just the construct he\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d seen before. Aspects of the staff that were lost when he looked too closely. Abruptly he got a System notification.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 <$Scr_Ps::0>Inferior Wizard Staff (Tier 1)}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Requirements to use: Level 1 or higher in any sapient race or Mana manipulation (Tier 1) Level 1 or higher.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Wielder can charge the staff with mana to create a bolt of destructive mana that can be fired at will. Additional mana may be used to either increase the damage inflicted or the effective range up to a limit of 10 mana per tier of the staff. Each mana dedicated to increasing the range will extend the range by one increment. Each mana dedicated to damage increases the damage inflicted by one increment. Damage type determined by aspect of mana used.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Range increment:  150 meters}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Congratulations! Skill Learned: Beginner Identify (Tier 1) Level 1!<!$Scr_Ps::0>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\ltrch\loch \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The Guide blinked. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Well, that didn\u8217\'92t take as long as expected.\u8221\'94 She shook her head. \u8220\'93Expert titles must have lowered the threshold for the System assist to kick in. So what shall we work on next?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The next several hours were spent on gaining system recognition for the stalking and fieldcraft abilities he had previously learned on the sniper course, the unarmed combat skills he picked up in basic training and various martial arts classes he took, and his skill at using a staff in melee. That was followed up with some additional training in mana theory and meditation that led into the Guide\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s assistance in creating an spell to shield himself from both physical and magical attack.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
